 a viable Iraqi state and recognize the challenges in bringing domestic reconciliation and normalcy to Iraqis. From Desolation to Reconstruction: Iraq’s Troubled Journey examines Iraq’s reality after the 2003 US-led invasion. It begins by relating Iraq’s modern social and political history prior to the invasion and then outlines the significant challenges of democratization and the creation of an Iraqi constitution, which will be necessary for Iraq to become a strong and effective state. Co-published with the Centre for International Governance Innovation (CIGI).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIraq War, 2003-2011. 0aPostwar reconstructionxIraq. 0aPostwar reconstructionzIraq. 4aHistory. 4aHistory: Military History. 4aPolitical Science. 7aHISTORY / Military / Iraq War (2003-2011).2bisacsh1 aAngulo-Pasel, Carla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrynen, Rex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCameron, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFantappié, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFunk, Nathan C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarrib, Aidan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLamani, Mokhtar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLamani, Mokhtar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMomani, Bessma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMomani, Bessma, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRomano, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSassoon, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSluglett, Peter, econtributor.